attributes.body:
I'm still here and doing this, but so far so good.

I've been getting a fair bit of work done, but also made the time to go on a tour, and go out dancing. I'll be sure to update this later with more photos when I leave.

photos.title: Wild Bird
photos.description: This unremarkable looking bird flew into the glass next to me while I was reading. He tried again immediately, and was immediately back on the ground. He paused. Not sure if he was just going to keep doing it, i went over, and surprisingly, he just let me pick him up. I held him there for about three minutes while he gathered his wits, and then he flew off, opting to go the opposite direction of the glass.

photos.title: Train
photos.description: An old steam train. An invention that revolutionized the valley.

photos.title: Looking Up
photos.description: I went on a great walking tour, which is where many of these photos are from. The tour guide said this was one of the best photos in MedelliÃÅn. It was worth  chuckle, but it does make a cool photo.

photos.title: Botero Horse Statue
photos.description: These oddly proportioned status by Botero are all over town.

photos.title: Mural
photos.description: This mural extended on for ages detailing history of the city.

photos.title: Church Interior
photos.description: A shot from the side where you can see  most of it. I kind of like this, even with the distortion of the panorama.

photos.title: Church Interior
photos.description: There are so many massive churches.

photos.title: Bird Bomb
photos.description: This statue was blown up in a public place about 20 years ago. A number of people were killed, but the status was left in place as a reminder.

photos.title: Metro Station
photos.description: The metro station is clean. The metro itself is quiet and one of the nicest public transit systems I've ever seen.

photos.title: Lift
photos.description: Due to the hills here, they've actually included a sort of gondola to take people home. This station connects directly to the metro. It's fun in and of itself.

photos.title: View from the Gondola
photos.description: Here's some of what we saw as we rode up.

photos.title: Tejo
photos.description: Tejo is a funny Colombian game. I guess it's a bit like horseshoes. You throw a metal disc at this clay thing. You can barely make out the steel ring, but the two pink triangles are right on top of it at the edges. You try to get it in the middle. The pink papers are actually pouches filled with gunpowder that explode when it, making the game exponentially more fun.

photos.title: Tejo
photos.description: This gives you a bit more of an idea of the place. You grab a beer, hang out and throw tejos around.

photos.title: Pasta Dinner
photos.description: We made a really nice chicken pesto pasta at the hostel. Everyone was happy.
